<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-286-122  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 286 122.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  May 8 1989 v3 n19 p10(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Air Force to upgrade missile control systems.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brewin, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The US Air Force will upgrade the computer and communicationssystems that run launch control centers for long-range nuclearmissiles.andP;  The project, which will cost $507 million, willstreamline authentication of war order messages as well as missileretargeting and launch authorization.andP;  The Rapid Execution andCombat Targeting (REACT) contract calls, for the first time, forautomation of processing of war order messages, placing anelectronic interface between war order messages and weapon controlsystems.andP;  An Air Force official says that nuclear assurednessaspects of the system remain as they were.andP;  'Man,' he says,'remains in the loop.'andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Command and Control SystemsUnited States. Air ForceDefense ContractsWeaponsMissilesSecurity.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>